<div class="slide">
    <h1>Simple Text Input - Collecting a single response from the user</h1>
    <ol>
        <li>Write a simple script that prompts the user for their age, with an appropriate question, then prints just the age to the screen. </li>
        <li>Extend the script so that it uses the concatenation operator to print the age fornatted with a suitable message</li>
        <li>Extension:  Extend the script further so that it also asks for the user's name, and prints a string in the format "Name is X years old"</li>
    </ol>
</div>

<div class='slide'>
    <h1>Using Format Characters in User Input Programs</h1>
    <ol>
        <li>Write a simple script that asks the user the following questions and then prints the responses in a single string at the end:
            <ul>
                <li>What is your name?</li>
                <li>What is your quest?</li>
                <li>What is the airspeed velocity of an unladen swallow?</li>
            </ul>
    </ol>    
</div>

<div class='slide'>
    <h1>Collecting some numbers and keeping a running total</h1>
    <ol>
        <li>Write a script that prompts the user (asking "How much did you spend" or similar) to enter how much money they spent, then print that number to the screen</li>
        <li>Extend the script so that it asks for 4 numbers, one after the other.  At each number it should add the number to the previous subtotal.  A single total should be displayed at the end</li>
        <li>Extension: Extend the script so that it it prints the subtotal each time an amount is added</li>
    </ol>

</div>

